This paper deals with image compression using a neural network, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of side information is also a key aspect of the paper, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to learn correlations between the encoder and decoder images, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or neural networks (cs.NE).
